# Form Handling Rules

## Frontend Forms
- Use React Hook Form for all forms
- Implement Zod validation schemas
- Use shadcn/ui form components
- Include proper error handling and validation feedback

## Form Layout
- Add space between labels and inputs as per user preference
- Use consistent spacing and typography
- Implement proper responsive design
- Use proper form field grouping

## Validation
- Implement client-side validation with Zod
- Use server-side validation in Django serializers
- Display validation errors clearly
- Implement proper field-level and form-level validation

## Form Components
- Use shadcn/ui form components consistently
- Implement proper form field components
- Use proper input types and attributes
- Include proper accessibility features

## Error Handling
- Display validation errors clearly
- Use proper error message styling
- Implement proper loading states
- Handle network errors gracefully

## Form Submission
- Implement proper loading states during submission
- Disable form during submission
- Show success/error feedback
- Handle form reset after successful submission

## Accessibility
- Use proper form labels and descriptions
- Implement proper keyboard navigation
- Use proper ARIA attributes
- Test with screen readers

## Data Flow
- Use controlled components
- Implement proper state management
- Use proper data transformation
- Handle form data properly